BUT 3hr fields only start in 2026. Similarly for ACCESS1-0.

For evaporation: has 3-hourly hfls (latent heat flux), which can be converted to
evaporation by dividing by latent heat of vaporisation (function of SST, daily output available, not much of a diurnal cycle so should be okay. Compare this to monthly evspsbl to make sure it's reasonable.)

GFDL-ESM2G: should be available but not all on raijin
HadGEM2-ES: should be available (except for ps, use monthly?) but not all on raijin

RCP_6h = climatology_mon (ERA-Interim) + RCP_mon (CMIP5) - climatology_mon (CMIP5) + RCP_6h (CMIP5) - RCP_mon (CMIP5)

i.e. climatology + monthly anomalies from climatology + subdaily anomalies from monthly, but swap out climatology with obs.

Option 2: Use submonthly variability from ERA-Interim:

RCP_6h = climatology_mon (ERA-Interim) + RCP_mon (CMIP5) - climatology_mon (CMIP5) + repeating 14-year subdaily (ERA-Interim) - climatology_mon (ERA-Interim)

i.e. monthly anomalies from CMIP5. could do multi-model mean as well as specific model (ACCESS1-3).
